s riches oil production generated. David A. Detomasi weaves together politics, geopolitics, and economics to provide a complete picture of how the system really works, and what direction it will take in the future. As the world becomes increasingly aware of the dangers and challenges oil dependency creates, knowledge of this crucial commodity has never been more relevant and critical for humanity’s future. Profits and Power will resonate with anyone interested in, or charged with responding to, our evolving energy future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aPetroleum industry and tradexEconomic aspects. 0aPetroleum industry and tradexHistory. 0aPetroleum industry and tradexPolitical aspects. 0aWorld politicsy21st century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Economy.2bisacsh  aChina energy.  aFracking.  aNatural gas.  aOPEC.  aRussian oil.  aUS oil production.  aemerging markets.  aenergy.  ageopolitics.  aglobalization.  aoil and climate change.  aoil industry.  aoil markets.  aresource curse.  aworld politics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076715540uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148751032940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487510329423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487510329/original  a978-3-11-076715-5  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles